<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<ApexClass xmlns="http://soap.sforce.com/2006/04/metadata">
    <apiVersion>48.0</apiVersion>
    <status>Active</status>
    <userStory>
        As a Salesforce user, I want to be able to view account and contact details in a Lightning web component, so that I can quickly access important information. 
    </userStory>
    <acceptanceCriteria>
        <criteria>When I access the Lightning web component, I should see a list of all accounts and their associated contacts.</criteria>
        <criteria>Clicking on an account should display details of that account, including its name, phone number, and address.</criteria>
        <criteria>Clicking on a contact should display details of that contact, including its name, email address, and phone number.</criteria>
        <criteria>The Lightning web component should only display accounts and contacts that are visible to the user.</criteria>
        <criteria>The information displayed in the Lightning web component should be up-to-date and accurate.</criteria>
    </acceptanceCriteria>
    <definitionOfDone>
        <definition>The Create AccountContactWrapper Apex class should be created with methods to retrieve and organize the necessary account and contact data.</definition>
        <definition>The Lightning web component should be designed with appropriate fields and labels to display the relevant account and contact details.</definition>
        <definition>The Lightning web component should be tested thoroughly to ensure that it displays the correct data for each account and contact.</definition>
        <definition>The Lightning web component should be integrated into the Salesforce system and made available to users.</definition>
        <definition>Documentation should be provided to explain how to access and use the Lightning web component.</definition>
    </definitionOfDone>
</ApexClass>